## ğŸ” DATA FLOW DIAGRAM

```plaintext
[ App.jsx ]
     â†“
[ PostProvider ] â† fetchPosts (GET /posts)
     â†“
[ PostContext ] â†’ posts, addPost, editPost, deletePost
     â†“
usePosts()
 â”œâ”€â”€ PostForm (for create/edit) â†’ POST / PUT
 â”œâ”€â”€ PostList
 â”‚     â””â”€â”€ PostItem â†’ DELETE
```

---

## ğŸ’» COMPONENT FLOW

### ğŸ”¸ `App.jsx`

* Uses `<PostForm />` for adding new post
* Uses `<PostList />` to display all posts

### ğŸ”¸ `PostContext.jsx`

* Holds all the logic: fetch, add, edit, delete
* Stores: `posts`, `loading`

### ğŸ”¸ `usePosts.js`

* Exposes context with a reusable hook

### ğŸ”¸ `PostList.jsx`

* Uses `usePosts()` to get `posts`
* Maps over each post â†’ `<PostItem />`

### ğŸ”¸ `PostItem.jsx`

* Shows single post
* Edit â†’ toggles `<PostForm />` with initial data
* Delete â†’ calls `deletePost(id)`

### ğŸ”¸ `PostForm.jsx`

* Reusable form for adding or editing
* Handles both POST and PUT based on props

